<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chapter-linear">
  <title>Linear</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This chapter is all about <q>linear</q> math expressions. An example of a linear math
      expression is <m>2x+5</m>. A linear expression like this could come out of a word problem, be
      on one side of an equation like <md>2x+5=7</md>, be part of a function formula like
      <m>f(x)=2x+5</m>, be graphed using the equation <m>y=2x+5</m>, or much more.
    </p>
  </introduction>
  <xi:include href="section-modeling-with-equations-and-inequalities.ptx"/>
  <xi:include href="section-linear-equations-and-inequalities.ptx"/>
  <xi:include href="section-slope.ptx"/>
  <xi:include href="section-lines.ptx"/>
  <xi:include href="section-linear-systems.ptx"/>
</chapter>

